==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lizards tail
<hw>Liz"ard's tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A perennial plant of the genus <gen>Saururus</gen> (<spn>Saururus
cernuus</spn>), growing in marshes, and having white flowers crowded in
a slender terminal spike, somewhat resembling in form a lizard's tail;
whence the name.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Llama</ent>⟦br⟧
